The dead guy,
he showed me him, like,

15:21.888 --> 15:24.989
grabbing somebody by the neck,

15:24.991 --> 15:27.692
a female, and holding her
up against the wall

15:27.694 --> 15:30.628
to the point where her feet
were, like,

15:30.630 --> 15:32.397
this much off the floor.

15:35.101 --> 15:37.968
Any idea who this dead guy
was in life?

15:37.970 --> 15:39.237
He was white.

15:39.239 --> 15:41.806
Like, max, I would say, 5'10".

15:41.808 --> 15:43.775
I see him with an older woman.

15:43.777 --> 15:45.743
There was abuse.

15:45.745 --> 15:48.679
So he lived here at some point,
and then he died.

15:48.681 --> 15:50.782
He didn't die here,
you know what I'm saying?

15:50.784 --> 15:53.717
But he's back here.

15:53.719 --> 15:56.254
And he's a big problem here.

16:10.737 --> 16:13.137
This is our third investigation
in Flint,

16:13.139 --> 16:15.573
so I've gotten to know a lot
of the local experts here.

16:15.575 --> 16:17.875
One historian
just called me back,

16:17.877 --> 16:20.211
and he said he found
a bizarre string of murders

16:20.213 --> 16:23.081
with a direct connection
to Chad and Carrie's property.

16:29.222 --> 16:30.654
Well, Walt, thanks
for meeting me.

16:30.656 --> 16:32.123
I really appreciate that.

16:32.125 --> 16:34.459
Now you mentioned on the phone
there was a sting of homicides

16:34.461 --> 16:36.126
connected
to my clients' property.

16:36.128 --> 16:39.530
Before we get to that, who owned
the land when this happened?

16:39.532 --> 16:42.533
Well, Steve,
the original landowner

16:42.535 --> 16:44.769
was Thomas Brandt.

16:44.771 --> 16:49.073
He owned over 70,000 acres
of land here in Genesee County.

16:49.075 --> 16:50.408
Okay, 70,000 acres.

16:50.410 --> 16:53.511
Was my client's house
and property even close

16:53.513 --> 16:54.812
to where this guy was?

16:54.814 --> 16:59.250
Yes. As a matter of fact,
Thomas Brandt's estate was here.

16:59.252 --> 17:02.186
Your client's property was
in this area here.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.654
Okay.
So this was pretty close.

17:03.656 --> 17:04.722
Yes.

17:04.723 --> 17:06.089
So what is the story
with the murders?

17:06.092 --> 17:10.261
Thomas' daughter, Charlotte,
in 1858, falls in love

17:10.262 --> 17:14.464
with a tenant farmer next door,
Davillo Palmer.

17:14.467 --> 17:17.067
Well, there are two problems
with this relationship.

17:17.069 --> 17:20.271
One, Charlotte's mother
does not approve,

17:20.272 --> 17:23.741
and two,
Palmer is already married.

17:23.742 --> 17:25.076
What happens with Charlotte?

17:25.078 --> 17:29.213
Charlotte turns up pregnant,
and not long after that,

17:29.215 --> 17:33.083
Davillo Palmer's wife suddenly
and mysteriously, disappears.

17:33.085 --> 17:34.551
Pretty convenient.

17:34.553 --> 17:37.955
Some accounts say that there was
a child who also went missing

17:37.957 --> 17:39.890
at the same time
as the mother.

17:39.892 --> 17:42.660
Were they able
to pin this on Davillo?

17:42.662 --> 17:44.228
Surprisingly, no.

17:44.230 --> 17:45.696
Murder was suspected,

17:45.698 --> 17:49.033
but they could never pin
any charges on Davillo.

17:53.172 --> 17:55.573
There's a little girl
running around here.

17:55.575 --> 17:57.975
She's probably
5 or 6 years old.

17:59.378 --> 18:02.480
She got, like, a little dress on
and then an apron thing on.

18:02.482 --> 18:05.249
So I would say, like,
that was...

18:05.251 --> 18:08.586
like, 1870s or 1880s.

18:08.588 --> 18:12.590
Something happened to her
that wasn't good,

18:12.592 --> 18:16.260
and I feel like
whatever happened to her

18:16.262 --> 18:18.395
happened here.

18:18.397 --> 18:19.797
Like, I'm seeing...

18:19.799 --> 18:22.066
So she's outside
and it's sunny.

18:22.068 --> 18:23.701
It's getting dark.

18:23.703 --> 18:26.337
She knows the person...

18:26.339 --> 18:28.573
and then she's dead.

18:30.343 --> 18:32.709
All right, so Davillo's wife
and possible child

18:32.711 --> 18:35.046
are out of the picture.
What happens next?

18:35.048 --> 18:38.916
Charlotte and Davillo
wind up getting married,

18:38.918 --> 18:40.551
and 6 months later,

18:40.553 --> 18:44.221
Charlotte's mother dies
under mysterious circumstances.

18:44.223 --> 18:46.057
What is the cause of death?

18:46.059 --> 18:49.627
The autopsy shows that she died
of arsenic poisoning.

18:49.629 --> 18:52.063
I mean, they already
like Davillo with one homicide.

18:52.065 --> 18:53.564
Did they look at him
for this one?

18:53.566 --> 18:57.235
He was a person of interest
in his mother-in-law's death,

18:57.237 --> 18:59.837
but he disappeared before
he could be indicted.

18:59.839 --> 19:02.840
So, Walt, we got at least
two murders, maybe three,

19:02.842 --> 19:04.442
pretty close to
my client's property,

19:04.444 --> 19:07.044
and nobody served a day of time
for any of it.

19:07.046 --> 19:08.179
That's correct.

19:14.019 --> 19:16.186
The little girl,
she sees a monster.

19:16.188 --> 19:19.991
It looked like
when tar is bubbling,

19:19.993 --> 19:23.427
but make it big,
like a human being.

19:23.429 --> 19:25.396
And is that something
that the living

19:25.398 --> 19:27.465
are affected by anyway,
or is it just her?

19:27.467 --> 19:30.067
That thing is the culprit
of everything.

19:32.338 --> 19:35.139
It seems like this monster

19:35.141 --> 19:37.341
went dormant until now.

19:37.343 --> 19:41.078
It has to have the people
that are predispositioned

19:41.080 --> 19:43.180
to the violence and the anger.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.182
So those living people
who move here

19:45.184 --> 19:48.986
who have that predisposition
triggers everything.

19:51.824 --> 19:53.357
So I just got a call back
from a sergeant

19:53.359 --> 19:54.859
with the local
police department.

19:54.861 --> 19:58.095
He says he found something
I definitely need to know about.

19:58.097 --> 20:00.564
Apparently, a pregnant woman
was found murdered

20:00.566 --> 20:03.501
less than a mile
from Carrie and Chad's house,

20:03.503 --> 20:06.571
and this remains
an unsolved case to this day.

20:06.573 --> 20:08.572
Now he's going through
all the records for me,

20:08.574 --> 20:10.575
and he's going to tell me
exactly what happened.

20:16.649 --> 20:19.116
Well, Sergeant, I appreciate
you looking into this for me.

20:19.118 --> 20:21.052
The body that was found close
to my client's property,

20:21.054 --> 20:22.153
what can you tell me
about it?

20:22.155 --> 20:23.120
Her name was Hope Johnson.

20:23.122 --> 20:26.323
She went missing
on January 29, 1988.

20:26.325 --> 20:27.858
Okay. So this is
a pretty cold homicide.

20:27.860 --> 20:29.459
Correct.

20:29.461 --> 20:31.128
She's a pretty girl.

20:31.130 --> 20:32.596
All right. So what do we know
about this girl?

20:32.598 --> 20:33.998
At the time
of her disappearance,

20:34.000 --> 20:35.199
Hope Johnson
was 8 months pregnant

20:35.201 --> 20:36.567
and had a 4-year-old son.

20:36.569 --> 20:39.537
She was last seen by her
boyfriend January 29, 1988,

20:39.539 --> 20:42.072
and he reported her missing
to the police department

20:42.074 --> 20:43.908
on February 2, 1988.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.476
How long
before they find her?

20:45.478 --> 20:47.345
Roughly 6 weeks after
she was reported missing,

20:47.347 --> 20:48.746
she was found on March 12th.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.547
Her body was found
on the side of the road,

20:50.549 --> 20:52.949
roughly 1 mile
from the client's house.

20:52.951 --> 20:54.518
Was the boyfriend a suspect
at all?

20:54.520 --> 20:57.154
We were not able to develop him
as a suspect in this case.

20:57.156 --> 20:59.623
They questioned a lot
of people.
Yes.

20:59.625 --> 21:01.425
Okay, and nobody
ever got arrested?

21:01.427 --> 21:03.294
No.
No one was ever arrested.

21:03.296 --> 21:05.495
Now I know it's an open case,
and you can't tell me anything

21:05.497 --> 21:09.032
about the details
of her murder.
Right.

21:09.034 --> 21:11.234
But when I worked these cases
in the past,

21:11.236 --> 21:13.237
it's always been
somebody they knew

21:13.239 --> 21:15.439
and a lot of rage involved.

21:15.441 --> 21:16.641
I just hope you guys
get a break on it

21:16.643 --> 21:18.242
because this is
a pretty sad case.

21:18.244 --> 21:21.445
Yes, very sad.

21:21.447 --> 21:24.314
Is this living man
being influenced

21:24.316 --> 21:26.250
by this tar thing at all?

21:26.252 --> 21:27.985
Yes.

21:27.987 --> 21:31.655
This is a child murderer.

21:31.657 --> 21:35.259
I think that this person

21:35.261 --> 21:37.628
is completely insane

21:37.630 --> 21:42.600
and probably
just thrives off of...

21:42.602 --> 21:46.070
violence and, you know,
gets its kicks off of that

21:46.072 --> 21:48.406
and is still capable
of doing it.

21:48.408 --> 21:51.709
I think that it could
be satisfied

21:51.711 --> 21:54.211
with an adult
killing another adult.

21:54.213 --> 21:57.014
I think that it probably
prefers children.

22:03.522 --> 22:05.622
For more information
about the show,

22:05.624 --> 22:07.290
and if you need us
to investigate

22:07.292 --> 22:09.159
unexplained activity
in your home...

22:09.161 --> 22:12.630
Please visit
travelchannel.com/thedeadfiles.

22:12.632 --> 22:14.698
Click on "Help me, "Dead Files!"
to submit your story,

22:14.700 --> 22:16.000
and we'll help if we can.

22:24.710 --> 22:26.110
So far, I've got clients

22:26.112 --> 22:28.179
being physically attacked
on a property

22:28.181 --> 22:30.514
where a man was suspected
of murdering his wife,

22:30.516 --> 22:33.917
mother-in-law, and possibly
even his own child.

22:33.919 --> 22:36.053
But I want to see
if there's anything else.

22:36.055 --> 22:38.589
Searching through old records,
I find an article about

22:38.591 --> 22:40.124
an auto plant
right down the street

22:40.126 --> 22:42.126
from Chad and Carrie's property.

22:42.128 --> 22:44.661
Turns out an employee
suffered a gruesome death

22:44.663 --> 22:45.830
while working there.

22:45.832 --> 22:48.032
I'm on my way to
the old Packard plant in Detroit

22:48.034 --> 22:50.167
to meet an autoworker
turned historian.

22:50.169 --> 22:52.403
Now he says he found a couple
of other deaths

22:52.405 --> 22:55.439
in the plants surrounding
Chad and Carrie's property.

23:01.547 --> 23:03.680
So, Gerry, that article
I found in my research,

23:03.682 --> 23:06.283
it sounds like this guy
died a pretty brutal death.

23:06.285 --> 23:07.585
What were we able to find out?

23:07.587 --> 23:10.287
That on October 3, 1963,

23:10.289 --> 23:12.356
a worker by the name
of Michael McDonough,

23:12.358 --> 23:13.724
who was 26 years old,

23:13.726 --> 23:16.927
died when a boom
struck him in the head.

23:16.929 --> 23:19.029
So, Gerry, let me ask you,
how far is this plant

23:19.031 --> 23:20.231
from my client's property?

23:20.233 --> 23:21.632
Less than a mile.

23:21.634 --> 23:23.366
Now does he die
right there on the spot?

23:23.368 --> 23:25.603
Normally,
in a General Motors factory,

23:25.605 --> 23:27.637
because of their insurance,

23:27.639 --> 23:30.307
that if you die
on the property,

23:30.309 --> 23:31.642
it's double a payout.

23:31.644 --> 23:34.578
So normally, most of them
that you will find,

23:34.580 --> 23:37.782
they're usually pronounced dead
in the hospital by a physician.

23:37.784 --> 23:39.449
Okay.

23:39.451 --> 23:40.918
There's no way this guy wasn't
dead when this thing hit him.

23:40.920 --> 23:42.452
Probably not.

23:42.454 --> 23:44.254
Now you mentioned on the phone
there was a couple other ones.

23:44.256 --> 23:45.522
What'd you find out?

23:45.524 --> 23:49.693
Found one in factory 31,
the axle plant, June 19th,

23:49.695 --> 23:51.929
and that was 1979.

23:51.931 --> 23:54.398
And this is a different plant
close to my client's property?

23:54.400 --> 23:59.269
Yes. John Holstein, who was
a 21-year-old worker.

23:59.271 --> 24:02.606
So a hydraulic line broke
and sprayed him down

24:02.608 --> 24:04.608
head to toe
with hydraulic fluid

24:04.610 --> 24:06.743
that was flammable
at that time,

24:06.745 --> 24:08.746
and a spark
from unknown origin

24:08.748 --> 24:11.848
is what turned him
into the human torch.

24:11.850 --> 24:14.418
And a witness to that,
it just so happens,

24:14.420 --> 24:15.619
was a friend of mine.

24:15.621 --> 24:18.622
And he seen him running
for quite some ways

24:18.624 --> 24:20.524
before he finally dropped.

24:20.526 --> 24:21.759
Did he die right away?

24:21.761 --> 24:24.561
He passed away 2 weeks later
in the hospital.

24:24.563 --> 24:27.631
Ouch. Now, Gerry, what else
were you able to find out?

24:27.633 --> 24:30.901
Another one at the Buick plant
in the body shop.

24:30.903 --> 24:34.572
It was on December 23, 1994.

24:34.574 --> 24:36.573
- It was Willy Anderson.
- Okay.

24:36.575 --> 24:38.042
And he was a die setter.

24:38.044 --> 24:40.978
He forgot to unhook a block --
80,000 pounds --

24:40.980 --> 24:43.380
and this die just
instantly crushed him

24:43.382 --> 24:47.251
between a guard rail
and the die.

24:47.253 --> 24:49.653
Before you became a historian,
you worked in this plant.

24:49.655 --> 24:50.988
Yeah.

24:50.990 --> 24:52.723
Were these accidents you just
described to me commonplace,

24:52.725 --> 24:55.526
or is it something that was,
you know, once in a blue moon?

24:55.528 --> 24:58.795
They were pretty commonplace,
and, at that time,

24:58.797 --> 25:00.998
speed was the name
of the game.

25:01.000 --> 25:03.267
We were trying to save
the Buick plant.

25:03.269 --> 25:05.068
And look where that got you.

25:05.070 --> 25:07.404
Yeah.
This is where we're at.

25:11.410 --> 25:14.878
I'm seeing a body on the floor.

25:14.880 --> 25:17.147
I think it's a man.

25:17.149 --> 25:20.650
I'm getting, like,
some chaos here.

25:20.652 --> 25:23.420
Like, I hear a woman crying.

25:23.422 --> 25:27.391
I'm hearing somebody
yelling for help.

25:27.393 --> 25:31.095
And I'm feeling, like,
a lot of people running around.

25:32.498 --> 25:33.864
Chaos.

25:41.173 --> 25:43.574
I saw several disturbing
things on my walk,

25:43.576 --> 25:47.912
but the violent dead man
had me very concerned.

25:47.914 --> 25:51.582
He did have a mustache.

25:51.584 --> 25:53.984
He had a thick, short neck.

26:00.459 --> 26:04.528
Next, I described the dead man
attacking a living person.

26:04.530 --> 26:07.397
He was showing me him, like,

26:07.399 --> 26:11.735
actually holding this person
above the stairs,

26:11.737 --> 26:14.271
and he was saying how

26:14.273 --> 26:17.274
he threw someone down there.

26:17.276 --> 26:19.143
I do believe it was a female,

26:19.145 --> 26:22.646
and that this person was
smaller than him.

26:29.188 --> 26:31.721
Amy, is this what you saw?

26:31.723 --> 26:33.424
Yes. that's what I saw.

26:53.245 --> 26:56.179
Now that Amy and I have
completed our investigations,

26:56.181 --> 26:58.281
we're ready to reveal
our findings to each other

26:58.283 --> 27:00.784
and our clients
for the first time.

27:00.786 --> 27:04.421
So, Amy, I'd like you to meet
Carrie and Chad.

27:04.423 --> 27:06.222
They live here,

27:06.224 --> 27:08.826
and they're raising these
four beautiful girls.

27:08.828 --> 27:11.161
This is Layla. She's 5.

27:11.163 --> 27:12.463
This is Tori, who is 10.

27:12.465 --> 27:13.797
This is Gabbie, who is 3.

27:13.799 --> 27:17.333
This is Ariana, who is 11.

27:17.335 --> 27:19.169
Now we're here, so obviously,

27:19.171 --> 27:21.338
you guys have a lot
of activity going on.

27:21.340 --> 27:23.673
But the big issue here is Chad.

27:23.675 --> 27:25.943
The whole family
is convinced he's changed

27:25.945 --> 27:27.677
since he moved in here,

27:27.679 --> 27:29.746
and if you can't help,

27:29.748 --> 27:31.615
they say it's going
to rip their family apart.

27:31.617 --> 27:33.149
With that being said,
I'm gonna ask Amy

27:33.151 --> 27:36.286
to tell us about her walk.

27:36.288 --> 27:41.691
When I first got here, I was
getting a lot of information.

27:41.693 --> 27:47.564
So I go upstairs,
and I saw two living females

27:47.566 --> 27:49.700
hiding behind a door.

27:49.702 --> 27:52.436
They were reacting
to a living male

27:52.438 --> 27:55.773
who was upset
and yelling and screaming.

27:55.775 --> 27:59.109
I felt such anger
from the living man.

27:59.111 --> 28:02.946
Like, he had murderous rage
coming out.

28:02.948 --> 28:05.983
This living male had
gone through a complete change,

28:05.985 --> 28:10.921
and I believe it's due
to an influence

28:10.923 --> 28:13.724
that's within this house.

28:13.726 --> 28:16.026
Wow. Carrie,
why don't you tell Amy

28:16.028 --> 28:17.795
how you feel Chad's changed?

28:17.797 --> 28:23.200
Before we moved in here, he used
to be a happy-go-lucky man.

28:23.202 --> 28:26.736
Now, he's very
just depressed and angry.

28:26.738 --> 28:28.672
So, Chad,
explain to Amy yourself

28:28.674 --> 28:30.140
how you feel you've changed.

28:30.142 --> 28:31.375
I don't know,

28:31.377 --> 28:36.379
but the range inside of me
comes over me heavy, fast.

28:36.381 --> 28:42.352
Sometimes, he just don't realize
that he is being very angry.

28:42.354 --> 28:46.156
It hurts me to hurt my family
in any direction.

28:46.158 --> 28:47.657
I'm seeing that you were

28:47.659 --> 28:49.359
in some dark situations
in the past,

28:49.361 --> 28:53.697
and that's making it easier for
what is here to influence you.

28:53.699 --> 28:55.499
My background ain't good.

29:00.906 --> 29:03.774
I saw an older man,

29:03.776 --> 29:07.978
and this older dead male
is extremely active.

29:07.980 --> 29:09.980
There's a lot of ways

29:09.982 --> 29:13.249
that living people
could experience him.

29:13.251 --> 29:18.722
I thought maybe you would see
him because he is very solid.

29:18.724 --> 29:20.990
Now, let's talk about
the tall shadow person

29:20.992 --> 29:23.126
that you mentioned to me.

29:23.128 --> 29:26.563
We will see him
shoot down the hallway.

29:26.565 --> 29:31.001
My children also see
this tall shadow man.

29:31.003 --> 29:33.237
He can also
be very physical.

29:33.239 --> 29:38.007
I had extreme neck
and head pain the entire time,

29:38.009 --> 29:40.210
and I saw him coming up

29:40.212 --> 29:43.313
and smacking people
on the back of the head.

29:43.315 --> 29:44.814
Carrie, do me a favor.

29:44.816 --> 29:47.451
Just tell her about how you were
getting grabbed in the shower.

29:47.453 --> 29:50.720
I have been grabbed
inappropriately in the shower.

29:50.722 --> 29:54.824
I've been grabbed in my bed.

29:54.826 --> 29:58.395
Now, Chad, you've been held down
in bed and choked, right?

29:58.397 --> 30:00.797
- Yeah.
- So tell Amy what happened.

30:00.799 --> 30:04.501
I couldn't move.
I was being held down.

30:04.503 --> 30:06.369
It was like being suffocated.

30:06.371 --> 30:09.840
Next thing I know, the bed is
in the middle of the room.

30:09.842 --> 30:11.341
Could that be this guy?

30:11.343 --> 30:14.311
Yeah. Definitely.

30:14.313 --> 30:15.846
There's nothing I can
do about it.

30:15.848 --> 30:17.781
That is what drives me
the most crazy.

30:17.783 --> 30:21.651
It angers me, and I've...
I feed off of it.

30:21.653 --> 30:24.388
I just want to get ahold of it.

30:24.390 --> 30:26.723
Can this guy do anything else?

30:26.725 --> 30:30.393
He can make you
really, really dizzy,

30:30.395 --> 30:32.996
and I just saw
people falling,

30:32.998 --> 30:36.466
and I also saw him
picking up a woman

30:36.468 --> 30:39.870
and throwing her down
the stairs.

30:39.872 --> 30:42.573
I did have a sketch done
of what I saw.

30:46.545 --> 30:49.713
When you take a look at this,
you'll know you're not crazy.

30:51.684 --> 30:53.483
Wow.

30:53.485 --> 30:56.353
My god.

30:56.355 --> 30:58.488
That is just insane.

30:58.490 --> 31:01.225
Do me a favor and describe
to Amy what happened.

31:01.227 --> 31:03.627
I was coming down the stairs,

31:03.629 --> 31:07.230
and I felt just
this big blow to my back,

